illustrated in Figure 3.

26
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:05,640
After filtration, air flows through heating 
and cooling coils where it is either heated  

27
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:10,080
up or cooled down to meet the required indoor 
temperature for both comfort and efficiency.

28
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:15,180
Heating and cooling coils are heat exchangers that
transfer temperature between steam and air in the  

29
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:19,200
case of the heating coil and between chilled 
water and air in the case of the cooling coil.

30
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:22,260
The humidifier and dehumidifier are optional parts  

31
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:26,160
of an AHU if humidity control 
of the indoor air is desired.

32
